30/03/2004
ATHENS, Greece -- Prime Minister Costas Karamanlis received a letter Monday (29 March from President George W Bush expressing support for Greece's efforts to make the upcoming Summer Olympics safe. Security was also the topic of talks Monday between senior Greek and US officials in Athens. The talks marked the end of a two-week joint exercise that included about 400 US special operations troops.
On Tuesday, the security chief for the Games, Peter Ryan, said "there is no direct threat against the Olympic Games or against Greece." He added that four times as many security officers would be in place, compared to the 2000 Summer Games in Sydney. (Macedonian Press Agency - 30/03/04; AP, Deutsche Welle - 29/03/04)
